      • INPUT_DATA_CALLED_REASON

        public static final String INPUT_DATA_CALLED_REASON
        Intents extra string that defines a default behavior for onHandleIntent(Intent). Intent.getIntExtra(String, int) can receive values:
        • INIT - it says that onHandleIntent(Intent) should process {initService() method as service assumed that it is it's first call.
        • BLUETOOTH - it says that onHandleIntent(Intent) should process {bluetoothService() method as service assumed that it was called by ConnectionPanel.toggleBluetooth_onClick(android.view.View)
        • WIFI - it says that onHandleIntent(Intent) should process {wifiService() method as service assumed that it was called by ConnectionPanel.toggleWirelessNetwork_onClick(android.view.View)
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
